# Markup documentation

## Two audiences

- **Maintainers** - XML and HTML comments are placed directly above the element or block they describe.
- **Consumers** - project README or docs/ for usage, and schema docs for public contracts when this repo publishes them.

Maintainer essays are not placed in user-facing pages. Run instructions are not placed inside markup files.

Only ASCII is used in maintainer comments.

## Maintainer block comments

`<!-- ... -->` is used. `[Label]` appears on its own line inside the comment, followed by a blank line, then an explanation (multi-line, no semicolons).

A short inline concept name may be added on the related element or attribute when a single line carries the setting.

```xml
<!--
  [Label]

  What this element or block does and when it is changed.
-->
```

For one-line notes only, `<!-- [Label] short note -->` is acceptable.

`[Past version]` and `[Past version - removed]` follow the same rules as in `code-doc-lang`. Past markup lines are listed first (each with an inline concept name), then a blank line, then an explanation.

## Public documentation

HTML and XML rarely use Javadoc-style API docs. Public structure is documented in README, OpenAPI, XSD annotations, or external specs, not in inline maintainer comments.

## When editing

- The smallest change that solves the task is made.
- Existing indentation and comment style in the file is matched.
